UML:TaggedValue.value: A Feature interpretation (or opinion) is a single consistent description of a Feature. This single consistent description may be the interpretation or opinion of a person or a software package (e.g., an instance in a time step). A Feature may have one or more FeatureInterpretations.

UML:Constraint.name: Should be used for any Features except the ones that have a dedicated interpretations objcts. Example : Faults should be interpreted by means of FaultInterpretation and Horizon by means of HorizonInterpretation.

UML:TaggedValue.value:
A Earth Model is a TRUSTY interpretation of the geologicalSite at one step of the geomodelling processus. A EarthModel points to a list of Organization ( only one organization by Organization kind) , each OrganizationKind can be builtupon an Other organization but it is not mandatory.
In particular when a WRITER want to be TRUSTED when he is delivering a "Earth Model" at the Stratigraphic OrganizationInterpretation Level, this organization must be built on A structuralOrganizationInterpretation which must be built on a tectonicOrganizationInterpretation, which must be built on a GeologicalSiteFrontierOrganizationInterpretation. A chain of references could be established if the model is tagged "TRUSTY" by a given Software)
